Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.55,0:03:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This plan was called "Sho: Part 1."
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.18,0:03:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a contingency plan, \Ndevised by a cornered IJN, to restore its position. {lit: recover the general trend}
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.79,0:03:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To be precise, using the aircraft carrier \NZuikaku as his flagship,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.06,0:03:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral Ozawa was to deploy \Nhis task force of 17 ships as a decoy
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.70,0:03:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,north of Luzon Island with the intention \Nof luring away the American TF 38.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.07,0:03:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, Kurita's Fleet \Nwas divided into two.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.92,0:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral Nishimura's 2nd Squadron was to pass through the Surigao Strait and infiltrate Leyte Gulf from the south. {technically fleet but i think they just missplled it, was sentai irl but they say kantai here, dai ni kaintai is kurita's force, not nishimura's}
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.10,0:03:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The main force of Kurita's Fleet, however, \Nwas to pass through the San Bernardino Strait
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.42,0:03:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and reach Leyte Gulf \Nby creeping along the coast of Samar.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.13,0:03:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, Vice Admiral Shima's 2nd Striking Force \Nwas to reinforce Nishimura's 2nd Squadron later. {I swear to fucking god, it's dai ni kantai again - I feel like whoever was writing this just couldn't bear to figure out those endless different fleets so he kinda gave up and was just naming any TF as kantai; it was originally dai ni yugeki butai}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.04,0:03:55.06,Sign,,0,0,240,,{\c&HD6DAE0&\b1\blur1\bord0}Episode 22 \N{\fs100}Battle of Leyte Gulf (Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.51,0:04:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, their voyage was a series of misfortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.04,0:04:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,First, having just barely entered \Nthe Palawan Passage on October 23rd,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.70,0:04:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the flagship Atago and the heavy cruiser Maya \Nsank after getting torpedoed by a US submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.25,0:04:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao was also all but wrecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Several Japanese cruisers approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.25,0:05:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack immediately! Attack and attack more!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on the 24th,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.45,0:05:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Sibuyan Sea, 260 combined sorties \Nby American carrier-based planes {from wiki: n all, five fleet carriers and one light carrier of Third Fleet flew 259 sorties with bombs carried by Helldivers and torpedoes launched by TBF Avengers against Center Force on 24 October, }
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.83,0:05:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,sunk the super-heavy battleship Musashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavy cruiser Myoko also came under attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.84,0:05:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.61,0:06:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop shooting the main battery! {HA's}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.26,0:06:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, even such heavy blows could not undermine \Nthe morale of the crews on the 23 remaining Japanese ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.18,0:06:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it was still possible for them to lure Admiral Halsey's "Big Blue Fleet" into a decisive naval battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On the dawn of the following day, the 25th, having skillfully passed though the demanding San Bernardino Straits, {/said to be difficult}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.78,0:06:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they emerged off the coast of Samar Island, \Nwhich commands the entrance to the Lamon Bay. {actually "Luzon Bay" but there's no such place so I think he actually means 14°33'03"N 122°07'27"E, but could be that big inland sea on 11°42'31"N 123°47'11"E}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.79,0:07:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The prelude to the Battle of Leyte Gulf, which we now know \Nas the IJN's most spectacular battle ever, was over. {/... was about to unfold}{not sure what to make of "japanese fleet's flashy fighting" - so added "ever" to make it make some sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.05,0:07:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is quiet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,50 more kilometers to Leyte. \NIt's like there's no welcoming party at all! {inadequately defended; undefended; unguarded; unprotected​}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they were tricked when we showed them \Nthat we're turning back into the Sibuyan Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.77,0:07:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.42,0:07:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, I wonder how is Ozawa's Fleet doing? \NWe haven't heard from them at all. {/what ... are doing}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.61,0:07:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We could check on them from the signal room. {no clue what he means: let's quickly go to the operation/strategy room and see}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.42,0:07:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. A signal from Kumano.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.73,0:07:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.54,0:07:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy ship at 110 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.16,0:07:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy fleet spotted! 125 degrees. Distance - 37,000!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's no way we could be that close to the enemy. \NAre you sure you didn't mistake it? Take another look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.33,0:07:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's there. There! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.83,0:07:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a carrier too. We're in luck! {grateful; thankful; welcome; appreciated; evoking gratitude​}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.89,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This alone makes coming here worth it! {これでやっとここまで来た甲斐があった}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief. Sir, we'll get them, won't we? {unsure what he means: is it okay to do}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If we see a convoy, we'll strike a convoy. \NIf a battlefleet shows up, we'll strike that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.77,0:08:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever we can get. {nc what he means: only doing - maybe "we'll hit everyone we see"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, we're finally doing it, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You idiot. What's there to cry about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.31,0:08:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They ran drill after drill, \Npreparing for a decisive battle with the enemy fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.62,0:08:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was never a battle between fleets, per se.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the order to attack a convoy was anticlimactic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they were happy to finally let the battleship Yamato see some action. {not sure what he means by "if you look at them" part: 輸送戦団攻撃を命令されていた彼らであってみれば戦艦大和として戦うことができる}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.30,0:08:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it was the IJN's cherished dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.64,0:08:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All ships into battle formation! {unsure what he means: all forces (could be full speed), immediately standing by; awaiting an opportunity; being on alert - }
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Line at 130! Turn to 110 degrees! {no clue whatsover, was "Line 130, fire direction 130 degrees" in HA; retsu is "row; line; file; column; queue; rank; procession" so I think it's some command somehow helping the ships form a line of battle, tenkai can be "expansion/advancement" or could be "turning/rotation" so I think it's also a command to form a line; total lit is "line 130, advancement/rotation direction is 110 degrees"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Line at 130! Turn to 110 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Japanese weren't the only ones \Nto discover their enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.45,0:09:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,American spotters from Sprague's Taffy 3 \Ncould now see them too. {Kurita's force caught Rear Admiral Clifton Sprague's Task Unit 77.4.3 ('Taffy 3') by surprise. Sprague directed his carriers to launch their planes, then ran for the cover of a rain squall to the east. He ordered the destroyers and DEs to make a smoke screen to conceal the retreating carriers}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This means... We're like a shooting gallery to the Japs! {lit is "target for shooting}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.27,0:09:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Dispatch all planes and set up a smoke screen. Order everyone to run for cover in that squall to the east!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.67,0:09:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, and give me the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.09,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the closest fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Task Unit 77.4.2, call sign Taffy 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.20,0:09:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Stump! Rear Admiral Stump! Sprague speaking! {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Felix_Stump#World_War_II}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.13,0:09:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.16,0:09:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's shoot! Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.23,0:09:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Still not there, sir? {no clue, maybe it's a statement}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.14,0:09:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The destroyer is still not in position? {lit: ... is not yet?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.25,0:09:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the tactics that Vice Admiral Kurita \Nhad drawn in his mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:09:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,battleships and cruisers would first wreck the decks of the enemy aircraft carriers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the destroyers could then \Nuse torpedoes to deliver a coup de grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.81,0:10:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Accordingly, they were now waiting \Nfor the destroyers to be fully in position. {lit: perfect formation}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.82,0:10:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.15,0:10:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! They're making their getaway. \NPlease let us shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.62,0:10:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Commence bombardment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.85,0:10:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.22,0:10:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,1 minute and 7 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.16,0:10:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.37,0:10:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's first super-heavy anti-ship cannon \Non the battleship Yamato was fired in search of its first prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.40,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes 1 minute and 7 seconds \Nfor a 1.5 ton shell to reach its target.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Plenty of time to change your course. {no clue whatsoever, nothing in HA either and whisper only has "前回の祈りの時間でもあった"; all I can hear is "also the time to ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.39,0:10:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.61,0:11:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,First shell landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.35,0:11:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We came under fire from their main armaments!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, they'll bulldoze us in no time! {lit: if this keeps up, it'll be the same as facing a tank in a business shirt}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.10,0:11:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.26,0:11:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sprague, listen! Don't give in to panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.61,0:11:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not leaving you to your fate. \NStay sharp, Sprague. Do what you have to! {unsure it's hema in the last one, lit is "don't do mistakes"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's not that bad, after all. {no clue whats last word, I hear "it's as though it's ... to the enemy"; ha had it as just "Amazing" lmao}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the time to relax. \NThey're just adjusting the range. {HA's, no clue what he means by "they're deciding where to land the bullet"; 着弾を決めているんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.38,0:11:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in a squall, sir. \NIt's like one big smoke screen for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't hit a target that we can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll stop soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.19,0:11:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the main US Fleet was already informed of the situation, Vice Admiral Kurita still had a free hand. {no clue what's shichuu here, rest is "もはや***に入ったアメリカ艦隊に栗田長官はまだ余裕があった" - "with the american fleet already/no longer entered/inside the shichu, kurita still had some leeway/allowance" - assuming they means "though Halsey's main battle fleet was already on their way back from Ozawa's decoy, Kurita had enough time to wreak havoc on convoys" but could be a completely different thing, was "Chief Kurita could still attack the US fleet that was within range." in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this squall had truly become a godsend \Nfor the US Navy, allowing them to prolong this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.68,0:11:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the American side used the pause to regroup \Nand increase their distance from Kurita's Fleet. {actually "change direction"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.96,0:12:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The screen of destroyers was finally set up. {lit: they've been able to put forward enough of destroyers}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.75,0:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Its finally our turn to retaliate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.35,0:12:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for the big one first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.60,0:12:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Their cannon has got to be ridiculously big!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Too big for its own good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.16,0:12:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when a shell does find its target, \Nit just pierces through with no damage. {legend: kurita's fleet was preparing for an engagement with a serious, heavy-armored fleet, but met this lightly armored convoy/support fleet, that's why they armor-piercing shells were literally coming through the american ships and out on the other side; he says "doesn't cause an explosion" - I think this also means that an armor-piercing shell doesn't cause a fire on board, as opposed to HE ones; no clue what's last part - kaetteraku - could be 'easy to return" but idk what it means, omitted altogether}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.29,0:12:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't it about time? {lit: we'll go soon}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.26,0:12:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavy cruiser ahead. \NDistance 18,000!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.27,0:12:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, attack with all we got!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.29,0:12:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy cruiser is approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.10,0:12:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some gutsy men among the Americans too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.01,0:12:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the battle off Samar \Nwas descending further into a free-for-all. {confused fight; free-for-all; melee; dogfight; scuffle; rough-and-tumble}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.32,0:13:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Starboard now! {lit is "turn around" so I think he means "let's shoot torpedoes from the other side"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, let's find another target now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.88,0:13:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.50,0:13:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where's the next Jap?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy has it in them. \NIt was a textbook torpedo attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedo spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.94,0:13:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Full to port!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:13:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Full to port!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.57,0:14:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedo spotted from starboard! {nc whats first word, assumed sagen}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.50,0:14:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A pincer movement?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.76,0:14:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Maintain the course!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.93,0:14:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like they're alive. {torpedoes?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't steer to the right or left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to follow their course \Nuntil the torpedoes run out of propellant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.77,0:14:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So they've driven us out of line of battle, after all? {unsure why he says "finally, we're leaving the ..." as if he was looking forward to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.27,0:14:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Chased away by torpedoes, \NYamato had to leave the line of battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.05,0:14:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The aircraft carriers Gambier Bay,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fanshaw Bay, Kalinin Bay, \Nalong with the destroyers Hoel, Samuel B. Roberts,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.39,0:14:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and Johnston, were either sunk or severely damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.33,0:15:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hits were also scored \Non the other 4 ships of Taffy 3, {actually he says "the measly 4 remaining ships were repeatedly hit/shot at" but that's complete bullshit: there was 6 more ships that he didn't mention, they weren't "remaining", they were all retreating together, finally it's straight up untrue: Raymond, John C. Butler, and Dennis were unharmed; also I love how he never even mentioned St. Lo which was sunk too}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.35,0:15:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who were trying to set up a smoke screen \Nas best they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.73,0:15:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Rear Admiral Sprague, \Nwho has been soliciting his allies for help all along,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.09,0:15:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,went all the way to the top and reached out to Vice Admiral Kinkaid, in charge of defense of the Philippines.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.16,0:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Kinkaid was far away from the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.92,0:15:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,While he was relieved, having wiped out Nishimura's Fleet, \Nan escort carrier stationed in the bay
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly came under attack from a Japanese fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were the Asahi and Kikusui units of the Kamikaze corps that sortied from Davao Base that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.32,0:15:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack of the Kamikaze corps paralyzed Vice Admiral Kinkaid, making him unable to dispatch a relief force.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.83,0:15:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, Sprague's fleet
