Dialogue: 1,0:16:11.78,0:16:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Halsey was also too far away.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:15.14,0:16:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When Halsey, who saw \Nthe enemy carrier fleet as their main objective,
Dialogue: 1,0:16:18.59,0:16:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was informed of the discovery of Ozawa's Fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he brushed off Vice Admiral Kinkaid's request for protection {actually "relief/urgent support" but at that time kinkaid didn't need it yet}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.25,0:16:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and steamed north in search of Ozawa's Task Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.44,0:17:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, Ozawa's Fleet brilliantly fulfilled its decoy role, \Nluring Halsey's fleet away from the actual fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.44,0:18:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One enemy aircraft carrier on fire!{first word could be kei which then makes it "light carrier"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.90,0:18:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Halsey, another telegram for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinkaid's complaints again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that, sir. A transmission from Admiral Nimitz \Nat the Guam HQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Nimitz want? Read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,WHERE IS REPEAT WHERE IS TASK FORCE THIRTY FOUR
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're fighting our asses off down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.39,0:18:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,THE WORLD WONDERS
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The world wonders?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.58,0:18:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean? \NDoes he think I'm dancing the hula-hula here or what? {not sure why he says "does he think I say something like hula dance"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.40,0:18:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.59,0:18:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nimitz and others don't know shit \Nabout what's going on here! {lit: nimitz is not to speak from position where one is not directly involved (in a matter); outsider's position; the sidelines}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.65,0:18:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.59,0:18:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Carney, we might as well help them out a little. {nc whats first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.44,0:18:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a real shame, though. I was looking forward \Nto seeing which trick Ozawa has up his sleeve this time. {/kind of hand Ozawa would play now}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.46,0:18:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, leaving Admiral Mitscher to handle the rest,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.42,0:19:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he personally led Task Force 34 back south.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, things went almost exactly as we planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.06,0:19:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugaki, we've finally done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. At last, Yamato's super-heavy gun \Ngot its chance to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, allow me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.42,0:19:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the enemy losses?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.25,0:19:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,3 to 4 enemy aircraft carriers are sunk, \Nincluding USS Enterprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.43,0:19:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus 2 armored cruisers. \NThe enemy has 1-2 carriers left at best. {actually just continues the list: as well as 1-2 carriers - but he just listed the carriers in previous line so wtf}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.33,0:19:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's left for us is to raid Leyte Gulf \Nbefore the enemy reinforcements arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, I was just considering our options...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:19:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:19:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't we done enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We got our long-awaited decisive naval battle. \NAnd we won it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.67,0:20:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it was a terrific struggle. {no clue, daisen is "great battle" but can't make out ka... in the end; was}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.46,0:20:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If we proceed to raid Leyte now, \Nthe relief fleet might really come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is also tenacious. If they encounter \Nour fleet in this condition, they could savage us. {not sure what's akire, could be "doesn't give up till the end"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, they might very well savage us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.08,0:20:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we have orders to raid the Leyte Gulf itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.69,0:20:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that. Should we press on now, \Nat risk of losing the rest of the Japanese fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.67,0:20:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or should we preserve it instead \Nto prolong the defense of Japan proper?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.09,0:20:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't stand for it. \NAfter making it this far, isn't it just one last push?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We're entirely in the dark on that matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.45,0:20:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How are things going on Ozawa's side?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.93,0:20:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For Nishimura's Fleet we only know \Nthat it was destroyed, but no details.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.37,0:20:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Where could the enemy be now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.38,0:20:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are our allies doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, there was no proper attempt to gather intel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We have nothing. \NAnd what became of Ozawa's Fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I have reasons to believe that this is a fake telegram. \NThe enemy produced it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.24,0:21:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A cleartext telegram from Halsey, saying \N"I'll go there in 2 hours."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll go to their rescue in 2 hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.65,0:21:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's a feint they often employ. \NIt's not unfamiliar to our side either. {maybe he means not the plaintext but the tactics of going to rescue later, tho I don't exactly see how they could do that often}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess we're in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.65,0:21:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, they did not yet know that Ozawa's Fleet performed its decoy role flawlessly, luring Halsey away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.78,0:21:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor did they have any idea \Nthat the Kamikaze corps' attack was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.67,0:21:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We should proceed to raid Leyte.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.15,0:21:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the whole point of the current operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not like this matter is for me to decide. {it is none of one's business; it is not one's place to say (do) something​}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it? Did you learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.02,0:21:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Still nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Reverse course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.34,0:21:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.03,0:21:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Full to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, what are you doing? \NThe enemy is that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.02,0:21:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, without ever entering Leyte Gulf,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.20,0:22:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Kurita's Fleet suddenly reversed course and withdrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.97,0:22:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese fleet retreats to the north!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.55,0:22:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.16,0:22:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Their move to reverse course and retreat \Nbefore ever entering the Leyte Gulf
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.08,0:22:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,surprised the Combined Fleet Headquarters \Nin Hiyoshi above anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:26.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H020B1E&\3c&HD9D7D6&\bord5}Combined Fleet Headquarters {連合艦隊總司令部}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.06,0:22:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately upon learning \Nof Kurita's Fleet reversing course,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.32,0:22:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they radioed out a telegram of encouragement. {encouragement; spurring (on); cheering (on)}
